<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 3:28AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONCERNS CONTINUE TODAY FOR WESTERN
MASSACHUSETTS...
A very dry airmass will combine with gusty northwest winds,
resulting in elevated fire weather concerns today. Specifically,
northwest winds will be sustained between 10 and 20 mph with gusts
up to 25 to 30 mph. Minimum relative humidities will range between
15 and 20 percent this afternoon.</description>
